25Z", "updated_at": "2015-08-29T12:17:30Z", "closed_at": "2015-08-29T12:17:30Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "When a struct contains an unsized member inside a nested struct, the error points to the start of a definition the top-level struct, rather than the member in a leaf struct which is the real cause.\n\n``` rust\nstruct nothere {\n  nope: f32,\n  nothere: Vec<f32>,\n  maybe: Vec<bad>,\n  guesswhere: f32,\n}\n\nstruct bad {\n  bad: [f32],\n}\n```\n\n> ```\n> <anon>:1:1: 6:2 error: the trait `core::marker::Sized` is not implemented for the type `[f32]` [E0277]\n> <anon>:1 struct nothere {\n> <anon>:2   nope: f32,\n> <anon>:3   nothere: Vec<f32>,\n> <anon>:4   maybe: Vec<bad>,\n> <anon>:5   guesswhere: f32,\n> <anon>:6 }\n> <anon>:1:1: 6:2 note: `[f32]` does not have a constant size known at compile-time\n> <anon>:1 struct nothere {\n> <anon>:2   nope: f32,\n> <anon>:3   nothere: Vec<f32>,\n> <anon>:4   maybe: Vec<bad>,\n> <anon>:5   guesswhere: f32,\n> <anon>:6 }\n> ```\n\nI'd expect error to point to:\n\n``` rust\nstruct bad {\n  bad: [f32],\n}\n```\n", "closed_by": {"login": "kornelski", "id": 72159, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjcyMTU5", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/72159?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/kornelski", "html_url": "https://github.com/kornelski", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kornelski/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kornelski/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kornelski/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kornelski/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kornelski/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kornelski/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kornelski/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kornelski/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.gith